# models/intermediate/int_deduped_channels.sql
```sql
-- Deduplicate customer_channels to primary attribution (earliest per customer)
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        customer_id,
        channel,
        attributed_at,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY customer_id
            ORDER BY attributed_at ASC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_customer_channels') }}
)
SELECT
    customer_id,
    channel
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

# models/fact/fct_revenue_by_channel.sql
```sql
-- Calculate customer revenue by attribution channel and city
WITH customer_channel AS (
    SELECT
        customer_id,
        COALESCE(channel, '(unknown)') AS channel
    FROM {{ ref('int_deduped_channels') }}
),
stores AS (
    SELECT
        store_id,
        COALESCE(city, '(unknown)') AS city,
        COALESCE(region, '(unknown)') AS region
    FROM {{ ref('stg_stores') }}
),
transactions AS (
    SELECT
        t.transaction_id,
        t.customer_id,
        t.store_id,
        t.amount,
        t.transaction_date
    FROM {{ ref('stg_transactions') }} t
)
SELECT
    c.channel,
    s.city,
    SUM(t.amount) AS total_revenue,
    COUNT(DISTINCT t.transaction_id) AS transaction_count,
    COUNT(DISTINCT t.customer_id) AS unique_customers
FROM transactions t
LEFT JOIN stores s
    ON s.store_id = t.store_id
LEFT JOIN customer_channel cc
    ON cc.customer_id = t.customer_id
GROUP BY
    c.channel,
    s.city
ORDER BY
    c.channel,
    s.city
